  <!-- Q1 -->
  <div class="qcard open reveal">
    <div class="qcard-hdr" onclick="toggleQ(this)">
      <span class="qbadge m7">7 Marks</span>
      <h3>What do you mean by critical section problem? Discuss Peterson's solution. <span class="ytag">2023</span></h3>
      <span class="qtog">▼</span>
    </div>
    <div class="qbody">
      <div class="ans">
        <div class="def"><strong>Critical Section Problem:</strong> A critical section is a segment of code that accesses shared data. When multiple processes access shared data concurrently, <em>race conditions</em> can occur — the outcome depends on the unpredictable execution order. The protocol must satisfy three requirements:</div>
        <div class="dw">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 640 90" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="640">
            <rect x="8" y="10" width="196" height="72" rx="9" fill="rgba(255,123,123,0.08)" stroke="#ff7b7b" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <text x="106" y="36" text-anchor="middle" fill="#ff7b7b" font-family="DM Serif Display,serif" font-size="13">Mutual Exclusion</text>
            <text x="106" y="56" text-anchor="middle" fill="#5a6880" font-family="Plus Jakarta Sans,sans-serif" font-size="11">Only 1 process in CS</text>
            <text x="106" y="72" text-anchor="middle" fill="#5a6880" font-family="Plus Jakarta Sans,sans-serif" font-size="11">at a time</text>
            <rect x="222" y="10" width="196" height="72" rx="9" fill="rgba(106,180,255,0.08)" stroke="#6ab4ff" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <text x="320" y="36" text-anchor="middle" fill="#6ab4ff" font-family="DM Serif Display,serif" font-size="13">Progress</text>
            <text x="320" y="56" text-anchor="middle" fill="#5a6880" font-family="Plus Jakarta Sans,sans-serif" font-size="11">If CS empty, any</text>
            <text x="320" y="72" text-anchor="middle" fill="#5a6880" font-family="Plus Jakarta Sans,sans-serif" font-size="11">requester can enter</text>
            <rect x="436" y="10" width="196" height="72" rx="9" fill="rgba(125,213,160,0.08)" stroke="#7dd5a0" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <text x="534" y="36" text-anchor="middle" fill="#7dd5a0" font-family="DM Serif Display,serif" font-size="13">Bounded Waiting</text>
            <text x="534" y="56" text-anchor="middle" fill="#5a6880" font-family="Plus Jakarta Sans,sans-serif" font-size="11">Limit on times others</text>
            <text x="534" y="72" text-anchor="middle" fill="#5a6880" font-family="Plus Jakarta Sans,sans-serif" font-size="11">enter before you</text>
          </svg>
          <div class="dlbl">Three Requirements for Critical Section Solution</div>
        </div>
        <h4>Peterson's Solution</h4>
        <p style="margin-bottom:10px;">Two shared variables: <code>flag[i]</code> (process i wants to enter) and <code>turn</code> (whose turn it is).</p>
        <pre><span class="cm">/* Process i — wants to enter critical section */</span>
flag[i] = <span class="kw">true</span>;            <span class="cm">// Signal: I want to enter</span>
turn    = j;               <span class="cm">// Yield turn to the other process</span>
<span class="kw">while</span> (flag[j] && turn == j);  <span class="cm">// Busy-wait if j wants in AND it's j's turn</span>
<span class="cm">/* ════ CRITICAL SECTION ════ */</span>
flag[i] = <span class="kw">false</span>;           <span class="cm">// Signal: I am done</span></pre>
        <h4>Why It Works</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Mutual Exclusion:</strong> If both want to enter, <code>turn</code> can only be i or j — exactly one must wait.</li>
          <li><strong>Progress:</strong> If j does not want to enter (<code>flag[j]=false</code>), i enters immediately without waiting.</li>
          <li><strong>Bounded Waiting:</strong> After i sets <code>turn=j</code>, j gets to enter at most once before i tries again.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Q2 -->
  <div class="qcard reveal">
