        <div class="def"><strong>Reader-Writer Problem:</strong> A shared resource (e.g., a database) can be read by multiple readers simultaneously, but a writer needs exclusive access. The challenge is ensuring consistency without unnecessarily blocking readers.<br>
        — <strong>First Readers Priority:</strong> Multiple readers can read simultaneously; writer waits for all readers. Risk: writer starvation.<br>
        — <strong>Second Writers Priority:</strong> If a writer is waiting, no new readers are admitted. Risk: reader starvation.</div>
        <div class="dw">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 600 130" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="600">
            <defs><marker id="adr" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" refX="3" refY="3" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L6,3 L0,6 Z" fill="#5a6880"/></marker></defs>
