          <li><strong>Binary Semaphore:</strong> Values 0 or 1 only — used for mutual exclusion (acts like a mutex).</li>
          <li><strong>Counting Semaphore:</strong> Values 0 to N — used to control access to a pool of N identical resources.</li>
        </ul>
